only 2 times..I speak Charlie Miller...dude you share....
we was and thank you for every minute brother,,,,HK how you did the magik!!!
BEST wishes from us all..sorry bout the name...!!

Never stop rockin' This is a good show with Donna strong to start yet Jerry's vocals are way down for a few songs.
First set is lively although the crowd seems a little impatient at times, which prompts some rebukes from the band here and there for patience.
Second set pretty good especially the Estimated >Eyes with a more Estimated twist to the transition and EYES goes heavy into a large scale DRUMZ.
Truckin is somewhat off to start but they jam it almost to meltdown. They choose pretty standard Wharf Rat>Round but both are well played.
(Not a fan of Donna's big scream in Around x2  but hey that's how it goes some nights)
U.S. Blues got overplayed in the encore slot. Still love the tune. Jerry pretty enthusiastic with the vocals
"I am going to steal your wife!!!"
"Better change your act"
"You can call this song the United States Blues"
MY MY OH MY OH MY OH.....
